column18: The PRMI analog was derived from the wild-type M58-66 peptide of the influenza A virus matrix protein.  This analog peptide contained a leucine at position 59 (I to L) and the bond between residues 58 and 59 was modified to NH-CO instead of CO-NH.  This retro-inverso modification represents an isosteric replacement of the amide bonds which confers greater biological stability.

Peptide M58-66 was derived from the amino acid sequence of the influenza A virus matrix protein.  The Leu <sup>59</sup>M58-66 analog was derived from GILGFVFTL wild-type sequence, by a substitution of position 59 (I to L).
